This paper deals with designing architectures and algorithms for a smart grid, which involves control and optimization of a complex system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves game theory and optimization, which suggests the category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the second most likely category. The paper also involves machine learning and decision making, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the third most likely category. The paper also involves artificial intelligence and optimization, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the fourth most likely category. Finally, the paper involves distributed computing and optimization, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the fifth most likely category.
